############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "contextCurrency.pl", "parserLinearRelation.pl", "randomPerson.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ $name = randomPerson(); $rate = random(4,8,0.01); Context("Currency")->flags->set(trimTrailingZeros => 1); $speed = Currency("$rate"); $initial = random(300,400,0.25); $start = Currency("$initial"); $final = random(600,800,5); $end = Currency("$final"); Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(t => 'Real'); $equation = LinearRelation("$initial + $rate t = $final");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Read the scenario. Then write a complete sentence that defines a variable to use. Lastly, write an equation to model the scenario. There is no need to solve the equation.
To save up for a new phone that costs [`[$end]\text{,}`] [$name] sets aside [`1\%`] of [$name->possessive] pay each week. This works out to [`[$speed]`] per week. At present, [$name->subject] [$name->have] [`[$start]`] saved up. How long will it be until [$name] has saved up enough? Write an equation to model this scenario. There is no need to solve it.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|t|]* as the variable.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{20}
END_PGML
